snippet.textDisplay:
I feel bad for wiley:

You got bars, you got the flow, the music is on point. You were one of the goats of early grime.

It's sad to see that such a 'goat' can't adapt to the ever changing flow of music. I mean, there was solid attempts like heatwave, but sadly Bro, they're one hit wonders for their time.

You also don't own grime, just because you 'did it first' that's a childish sentiment.

It's also sad because I can no longer see you as a musician, as feeling outraged someone would copy you isn't something real musicians do, someone using your flow and changing it doesn't make them a copycat. It makes you an influencer.

Keep doing what you're doing and that's fine Bro, just know that your influence will continue to die down as you age, or adapt to the interest and change in music to diversify and extend your careers life.

It's what real hungry musicians do.
